title: Bitcoin - to the rescue
description: Bitcoin was the first to solve the state problem in a decentralized way.
i18nReady: true
---

### Bitcoin

The Bitcoin protocol (a decentralized digital currency) introduced 2009 a system that allows the transfer of value without the need for a centralized entity.
It is a peer-to-peer network that allows the transfer of value from one person to another without the need for a third party.
But how did they manage the state problem? How did they manage that everyone agreed on who owns what and who has the right to do what?
